manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Note: Below is the list of phones that can be charged at max 3A output current instead of full speed: 1.Google Pixel: Only supports the private fast charge protocol of Google 2.OnePlus: Only support DASH fast charge protocol 3.Nintendo Switch: Only supports PD fast charge protocol 4.iPad Pro 2018/2020: Requires a USB C to C cable to fast charge 5.Samsung Galaxy Note 10/S20 plus: Requires a QC / AFC protocol charger with a 18W USB A port(The original charger is a PD fast charging with a 25W USB C Port)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love the length
reviews.reviewText: Funny how we went from 3ft, to 6, to 10 & now 15. Sitting on the couch, even the 10ft would get pulled out of the charging block (no close outlet) but with the 15ft, we don't have that issue.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars The cord lasted 5 months with using ut at bedtime
reviews.reviewText: I was really impressed with the quality after having bad luck with cables purchased elsewhere, but im not sure how long a cable should last. It definitely outlasted other "value" or "good deal" cables purchased elsewhere, that being said one went out after close to 5 months of using nightly to charge my phone. It stayed plugged in my bedroom, no moving it around all the time. So bottom line, i was impressed that this one lasted THAT long.Loved the length of it! Good value even at 5 months use just seems such a shame that cables are practically disposable in this day and age
